description: From Spanish cucaracha (“woodlouse”), from cuca (“butterfly caterpillars”), of onomatopoeic origin; see also Greek κόκκυξ (kókkux) and Late Latin cucus. Influenced, via folk etymology, by cock and roach. Doublet of cucaracha.

entries.meaning: A black or brown straight-winged insect of the order Blattodea.
(slang, offensive) A person or a member of a group of people regarded as undesirable and rapidly procreating.
(offensive, slang, ethnic slur, Rwanda) A Tutsi.
(Australia, slang, derogatory, humorous) A person from New South Wales.
(Australia, slang, obsolete) A hard lump of brown sugar.
